    <h3>Pastor and Founder W. Trey Davis</h3>
    <p>W. Trey Davis is the Senior Pastor and founder of Abundant Faith Fellowship Church “The House of Abundance”. He founded the church on March 2, 2014 with the view of simply transforming lives and building faith based on the Word of God. Pastor Davis currently holds a Bachelors of Arts Degree in Fine Arts from Texas Southern University, as well as a teaching certificate in General Education from the state of Texas. Additionally, he was licensed and ordained into the Gospel Ministry under Bishop Bill Hines, Jr., at New Covenant Christian Church in Houston, TX. His future academic plans include attending Houston Graduate School of Theology to pursue his Masters of Divinity.</p>
    <p>Pastor is married to Lady LaToya C. Davis, and they have two beautiful daughters; Meghan Elyse and Kirstyn Naomi. Some of Pastor’s hobbies include playing musical instruments, bowling, singing, traveling, and golfing. However, his greatest passion is sharing the Gospel of Jesus Christ through the preaching and teaching of God’s Word and musical expression.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <h3>Co-Founder and First Lady LaToya C. Davis</h3>
    <p>LaToya C. Davis is the founding First Lady of Abundant Faith Fellowship Church “The House of Abundance”. Lady Davis currently holds a Bachelors of Science Degree in Child Development from Texas Southern University, as well as a Masters of Education in Advanced Literacy from Concordia University. Her future plans are to pursue her Doctorate in Education, as well as provide extensive mentorship to young at-risk women.</p>
    <p>Lady “D” is married to Pastor W. Trey Davis, and is the proud mother of two lovely daughters; Meghan Elyse and Kirstyn Naomi. Lady “D” enjoys singing, traveling, and reading. However, her greatest passion is her family and ministering side-by-side with her husband.</p>
